The provided code chunk contains two methods (`popupGridDialog` and `toggleGridSnap`) related to managing grid settings within a state machine visualization tool, likely part of the FSM Inspector class that handles visual representation and interaction with finite state machines. These methods allow users to adjust grid spacing and toggle grid snapping functionality for positioning states on a canvas.

def popupGridDialog(self):
        spacing = askstring('ClassicFSM Grid Spacing', 'Grid Spacing:')
        if spacing:
            self.setGridSize(spacing)
            self._gridSize = spacing

    def toggleGridSnap(self):
        if self._fGridSnap.get():
            self.setGridSize(self._gridSize)
        else:
            self.setGridSize(0)
